<title>USA: Apartment Investment files $1 bln shelf.</title>
<headline>Apartment Investment files $1 bln shelf.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-05-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Apartment Investment and Management Co on Friday filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission for a shelf offering of up to $1 billion in debt securities, preferred shares and Class A common stock warrants.</p>
<p>The Denver-based real estate investment trust said it would use proceeds from the sale for general corporate purposes and working capital needs.</p>
<p>No underwriters were named in the filing.</p>
